From be296f7ef9c16933df91ebe9f008f3a0bb6a51d1 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Yi Ding <yi.s.ding@gmail.com>
Date: Wed, 1 Jul 2026 06:21:31 -0700
Subject: [PATCH 18/65] media: rockchip: rkvdec2-link: test per-core disable
 flag

Plain-language impact:
Disabled decoder cores are no longer added to the CCU work-mode mask by mistake.

Kernel details:
rkvdec2_hard_ccu_enqueue() iterates queue->cores as core but tested the outer mpp->disable. Test core->disable instead.

Source: split from patches/cleanup-draft after docs/11-bsp-audit.md verification.
Signed-off-by: Yi Ding <yi.s.ding@gmail.com>
---
 drivers/video/rockchip/mpp/mpp_rkvdec2_link.c | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/drivers/video/rockchip/mpp/mpp_rkvdec2_link.c b/drivers/video/rockchip/mpp/mpp_rkvdec2_link.c
index 79984d51898a..3d0da24bdc56 100644
--- a/drivers/video/rockchip/mpp/mpp_rkvdec2_link.c
+++ b/drivers/video/rockchip/mpp/mpp_rkvdec2_link.c
@@ -2606,7 +2606,7 @@ static int rkvdec2_hard_ccu_enqueue(struct rkvdec2_ccu *ccu,
 			struct rkvdec2_dev *dec = to_rkvdec2_dev(core);
 			struct rkvdec_link_dev *link_dec = dec->link_dec;
 
-			if (mpp->disable)
+			if (core->disable)
 				continue;
 			work_mode |= dec->core_mask;
 			rkvdec2_ccu_link_fix_rcb_regs(dec);
-- 
2.53.0

